su_text: Upami dosana asal ti Yonatan atanapi ti abdi, mugi diwaler ku Urim.
tgt_text: If this sin has been committed by me or by my son Jonathan, then, OLordGod of Israel, respond with Urim.

su_text: Upami asal ti rahayat Israil, mugi diwaler ku Tumim." Waleranana nunjukna ka Yonatan jeung Saul, jalma rea bebas.
tgt_text: But if this sin has been committed by your people Israel, respond with Thummim." Then Jonathan and Saul were indicated by lot, while the army was exonerated.

su_text: Saul unjukan ka PANGERAN Allah Israil, "Nun PANGERAN, naon margina Gusti henteu kersa ngawaler?
tgt_text: Then Saul said, "OLordGod of Israel!

su_text: Saul nimbalan deui, "Pilih antara kami jeung Yonatan." Anu katujul Yonatan.
tgt_text: Then Saul said, "Cast the lot between me and my son Jonathan!" Jonathan was indicated by lot.

su_text: Saul mariksa ka Yonatan, "Hidep nyieun salah naon?" Wangsul Yonatan, "Neda madu saeutik.
tgt_text: So Saul said to Jonathan, "Tell me what you have done." Jonathan told him, "I used the end of the staff that was in my hand to taste a little honey.

su_text: Timbalan Saul, "Ama sing disiksa ku Allah mun hidep ku Ama henteu dipaehan."
tgt_text: Saul said, "God will punish me severely if Jonathan doesn't die!"

su_text: Tapi balad arunjukan, "Baruk Yonatan anu parantos ngalantarankeun urang Israil unggul sakieu ageungna, bade dipaehan?
tgt_text: But the army said to Saul, "Should Jonathan, who won this great victory in Israel, die?

su_text: Sagala damelna dinten ieu estu kalayan panuyun Allah." Kitu Yonatan dibela ku rahayat, henteu jadi dipaehan.
tgt_text: For it is with the help of God that he has acted today." So the army rescued Jonathan from death.

su_text: Sanggeus Saul jadi raja Israil, anjeunna terus merangan musuh-musuhna di mana-mana: Urang Moab, urang Amon, urang Edom, raja-raja Soba jeung urang Pelisti.
tgt_text: After Saul had secured his royal position over Israel, he fought against all their enemies on all sides - the Moabites, Ammonites, Edomites, the kings of Zobah, and the Philistines.

su_text: Unggal perang di mana-mana unggul bae.
tgt_text: In every direction that he turned he was victorious.

su_text: Putra-putra Saul anu pameget nya eta: Yonatan, Iswi jeung Malkisua.
tgt_text: The sons of Saul were Jonathan, Ishvi, and Malki-Shua.

su_text: Anu istri, nu kahiji Merab, nu kadua Mikal.
tgt_text: He had two daughters; the older one was named Merab and the younger Michal.

su_text: Panglima perangna kapirayina, Abner, putra emangna anu jenengan Ner.
tgt_text: The name of the general in command of his army was Abner son of Ner, Saul's uncle.

su_text: Ari geureuhana Ahinoam binti Ahimaas.
tgt_text: The name of Saul's wife was Ahinoam, the daughter of Ahimaaz.

su_text: Ari Kis, ramana Saul, jeung Ner, ramana Abner, duanana putra Abiel.
tgt_text: Kish was the father of Saul, and Ner the father of Abner was the son of Abiel.

su_text: Sirah Goliat ku Daud dijingjing ka Yerusalem, ari pakarangna terus disimpen di kemahna.
tgt_text: David took the head of the Philistine and brought it to Jerusalem, and he put Goliath's weapons in his tent.

su_text: Basa Daud enggeus jung arek ngalawan Goliat, Saul mariksa ka Abner panglima perangna, saurna, "Abner, anak saha eta teh?" Wangsul Abner, "Duka Gusti, abdi teu terang."
tgt_text: Now as Saul watched David going out to fight the Philistine, he asked Abner, the general in command of the army, "Whose son is this young man, Abner?" Abner replied, "As surely as you live, O king, I don't know."

su_text: Samulangna ka pasanggrahan tas ngarubuhkeun Goliat, Daud ku Abner dideuheuskeun deui ka Saul.
tgt_text: So when David returned from striking down the Philistine, Abner took him and brought him before Saul.

su_text: Ku Saul dipariksa, "Ari hidep anak saha?" Wangsul Daud, "Dawuh Gusti, abdi pecilna Isai rahayat Gusti ti Betlehem."
tgt_text: Saul said to him, "Whose son are you, young man?" David replied, "I am the son of your servant Jesse in Bethlehem."

tgt_text: The descendants of Aaron were also allotted as cities of refuge Hebron, Libnah and its pasturelands, Jattir, Eshtemoa and its pasturelands,

tgt_text: Within the territory of the tribe of Benjamin they were allotted Geba and its pasturelands, Alemeth and its pasturelands, and Anathoth and its pasturelands.

tgt_text: Their clans were allotted thirteen cities in all.

su_text: Golongan Kahat salian ti eta maratuhna di wewengkon Menase Kulon, sapuluh kota anu elotna ragrag ka maranehna, sakulawarga sakota.
tgt_text: The rest of Kohath's descendants were allotted ten cities in the territory of the half-tribe of Manasseh.

su_text: Golongan Gerson meunang tilu belas kota di wewengkon Isaskar, Aser, Naptali, jeung di Basan anu ayana di wewengkon Menase Wetan, sakulawarga sakota.
tgt_text: The clans of Gershom's descendants received thirteen cities within the territory of the tribes of Issachar, Asher, Naphtali, and Manasseh (in Bashan).

su_text: Golongan Merari nya kitu keneh, meunang dua belas kota di wewengkon Rubin, Gad jeung Sebulun, sakulawarga sakota.
tgt_text: The clans of Merari's descendants were allotted twelve cities within the territory of the tribes of Reuben, Gad, and Zebulun.

su_text: Ku jalan kitu kaom Lewi ti urang Israil mareunang tempat pamatuhan katut tanah-tanah sampalanana.
tgt_text: So the Israelites gave to the Levites these cities and their pasturelands.

su_text: (Kota-kota di wewengkon Yuda, Simeon jeung Binyamin anu ditataan bieu, dibagikeunana kabeh ku jalan dilotre.)
tgt_text: They allotted these previously named cities from the territory of the tribes of Judah, Simeon, and Benjamin.

su_text: Tesalonika 1
tgt_text: Tesalonika 1

su_text: Sim kuring terang dulur-dulur, aranjeun teh ku Allah dipikaasih, dipilih jadi kagungana-Na ku manten.
tgt_text: We know, brothers and sisters loved by God, that he has chosen you,

su_text: Sabab sim kuring mawa Injil Kasalametan ka aranjeun teh lain ku caritaan bae, tapi kasartaan ku daya jeung Roh Suci, bari yakin sayakin-yakinna yen eta Injil Kasalametan teh bener.
tgt_text: in that our gospel did not come to you merely in words, but in power and in the Holy Spirit and with deep conviction (surely you recall the character we displayed when we came among you to help you).

su_text: Ku hal eta aranjeun teh geus dipiconto ku sakabeh dulur sakapercayaan di Makedoni jeung Ahaya.
tgt_text: As a result you became an example to all the believers in Macedonia and in Achaia.

su_text: Sabab anu sumebar di sakuliah Makedoni jeung Ahaya teh lain ngan wawaran hal eta bae, iman aranjeun ka Allah oge milu kagurnita ka mana-mana, nepi ka sim kuring geus teu bisa nyaritakeunana.
tgt_text: For from you the message of the Lord has echoed forth not just in Macedonia and Achaia, but in every place reports of your faith in God have spread, so that we do not need to say anything.

su_text: sarta ngarep-ngarep sumping putra-Na ti sawarga, nya eta Yesus, anu ku Mantenna geus digugahkeun ti nu paraeh, anu nyalametkeun urang tina hukuman Allah engke.
tgt_text: and to wait for his Son from heaven, whom he raised from the dead, Jesus our deliverer from the coming wrath.

su_text: Negeran, ngalilipur, jeung ngadorong supaya hirup aranjeun sapagodos jeung pangersa Allah, anu geus nyaur aranjeun kana Karajaan jeung kamulyaana-Na.
tgt_text: exhorting and encouraging you and insisting that you live in a way worthy of God who calls you to his own kingdom and his glory.

su_text: Jeung kieu nu matak sim kuring muji sukur ka Allah teh: Eta amanat ti Allah anu ditepikeun ku sim kuring teh ku aranjeun ditarima jeung dipercaya, yen lain beja ti manusa, tapi amanat ti Allah.
tgt_text: And so we too constantly thank God that when you received God's message that you heard from us, you accepted it not as a human message, but as it truly is, God's message, which is at work among you who believe.

su_text: Anu kaalaman ku aranjeun teh, dulur-dulur, sarua jeung anu kaalaman ku jamaah Allah di Yudea, ku jelema-jelema anu geus jadi milikna Kristus Yesus.
tgt_text: For you became imitators, brothers and sisters, of God's churches in Christ Jesus that are in Judea, because you too suffered the same things from your own countrymen as they in fact did from the Jews,

su_text: anu geus maehan Gusti Yesus jeung nabi-nabi-Na, jeung nganiaya rasul-rasul-Na.
tgt_text: who killed both the Lord Jesus and the prophets and persecuted us severely.

su_text: Nya aranjeun anu bisa ngabungahkeun hate jeung ngagedekeun harepan sim kuring, jeung anu bisa diagulkeun ku sim kuring ka payuneun Yesus Gusti urang, engke ari Anjeunna geus sumping.
tgt_text: For who is our hope or joy or crown to boast of before our Lord Jesus at his coming?

su_text: Mugia Allah anu maparin katengtreman ka urang sing nyucikeun tingkah laku aranjeun, sangkan suci sakujur diri, jiwa, nyawa, jeung raga, sing ulah aya celana dina waktu sumping Gusti urang Yesus Kristus.
tgt_text: Now may the God of peace himself make you completely holy and may your spirit and soul and body be kept entirely blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.

su_text: Ieu surat, demi Gusti, pangmacakeun ka sakabeh dulur sakapercayaan.
tgt_text: I call on you solemnly in the Lord to have this letter read to all the brothers and sisters.

su_text: Mugia dulur-dulur ginanjar rahmatna Gusti urang Yesus Kristus.
tgt_text: The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.

su_text: Timotius 1
tgt_text: Timotius 1

su_text: Nasehatna tujukeun pikeun mulihkeun deui sipat kanyaah anu bijil tina ati sanubari, medal tina pikiran nu caang, mencar tina kaiklasan iman.
tgt_text: But the aim of our instruction is love that comes from a pure heart, a good conscience, and a sincere faith.

su_text: Eta teh harayangeun jadi guru agama, tapi kana omonganana sorangan teu ngarti, kana hal anu ku maranehna diajarkeun bangun sakitu yakinna teh maranehna sorangan teu paham.
tgt_text: They want to be teachers of the law, but they do not understand what they are saying or the things they insist on so confidently.

su_text: Ngan inget, Hukum Agama dijieunna teh lain keur jelema anu balageur, tapi keur tukang rerempak, keur penjahat, keur nu baragajul, keur nu doraka, keur nu teu boga agama, keur nu teu malire kana sual rohani, keur jelema anu maehan bapa atawa indung, sarta keur tukang-tukang maraehan umumna,
tgt_text: realizing that law is not intended for a righteous person, but for lawless and rebellious people, for the ungodly and sinners, for the unholy and profane, for those who kill their fathers or mothers, for murderers,

su_text: keur nu teu boga ahlak, keur nu cabul patemon, keur culik, keur tukang bohong, keur nu sok mere panyaksi palsu, jeung sajaba ti eta anu ingkar tina pangajaran anu bener,
tgt_text: sexually immoral people, practicing homosexuals, kidnappers, liars, perjurers - in fact, for any who live contrary to sound teaching.

su_text: Bapa muji sukur ka Kristus Yesus Gusti urang, sabab ku berkah Anjeunna bapa kuat ngajalankeun kawajiban.
tgt_text: I am grateful to the one who has strengthened me, Christ Jesus our Lord, because he considered me faithful in putting me into ministry,

su_text: Kalimah, "Kristus Yesus sumping ka dunya pikeun nyalametkeun jalma dosa" teh memang wajib dipercaya sabab enya.
tgt_text: This saying is trustworthy and deserves full acceptance: "Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners" - and I am the worst of them!

su_text: ku Allah dipikawelas, supaya Kristus Yesus iasa nembongkeun kasabarana-Na anu taya hinggana ka bapa, jalma pangdorakana, pikeun jadi conto ka sakabeh jalma anu bakal palercaya ka Anjeunna pikeun narima hirup langgeng.
tgt_text: But here is why I was treated with mercy: so that in me as the worst, Christ Jesus could demonstrate his utmost patience, as an example for those who are going to believe in him for eternal life.

su_text: Amin.
tgt_text: Amen.

su_text: Kamulyaan, kaagungan, kasanggakeun sapapaosna ka Mantenna, Raja abadi, gaib, Allah anu maha esa.
tgt_text: Now to the eternal king, immortal, invisible, the only God, be honor and glory forever and ever!

su_text: Ku lantaran hidep geringan, nginum ulah cai wungkul, perlukeun saeutik mah nginum anggur keur ngabantu padaharan.
tgt_text: (Stop drinking just water, but use a little wine for your digestion and your frequent illnesses.)

su_text: Yohanes 1
tgt_text: Yohanes 1

su_text: Tah anu bareto katenjo jeung kadenge teh ku bapa diwartakeun deuih ka aranjeun, supaya aranjeun oge cara bapa, hirup dina kasatunggalan jeung anu jumeneng Rama kitu deui jeung Yesus Kristus Putra-Na.
tgt_text: What we have seen and heard we announce to you too, so that you may have fellowship with us (and indeed our fellowship is with the Father and with his Son Jesus Christ).

su_text: Maksud bapa nuliskeun hal ieu teh supaya kabungahan urang bisa tutug.
tgt_text: Thus we are writing these things so that our joy may be complete.

su_text: Eta warta ti Allah, anu ku bapa sabatur-batur katarima ti Putra-Na, sarta anu ayeuna di tepikeun ka aranjeun, nya eta: Allah teh Cahaya Caang, di Mantenna sama sakali teu aya poek.
tgt_text: Now this is the gospel message we have heard from him and announce to you: God is light, and in him there is no darkness at all.

su_text: Jadi lamun urang ngakukeun geus aya dina kasatunggalan jeung Mantenna tapi hirup di nu poek, eta teh bohong nya ucap nya lampah.
tgt_text: If we say we have fellowship with him and yet keep on walking in the darkness, we are lying and not practicing the truth.

su_text: Lamun hirup urang geus di nu caang sakumaha Mantenna anu jadi Cahaya Caang, eta ciri diri urang geus beresih tina dosa ku karana getih Yesus Putra-Na, sarta bakal bisa hirup sabeungkeut jeung pada batur.
tgt_text: But if we walk in the light as he himself is in the light, we have fellowship with one another and the blood of Jesus his Son cleanses us from all sin.

su_text: Lamun urang ngakukeun teu boga dosa, eta ngabobodo maneh, sarta Allah teu linggih di jero hate urang.
tgt_text: If we say we do not bear the guilt of sin, we are deceiving ourselves and the truth is not in us.

tgt_text: So Arioch quickly ushered Daniel into the king's presence, saying to him, "I have found a man from the captives of Judah who can make known the interpretation to the king."

tgt_text: The king then asked Daniel (whose name was also Belteshazzar), "Are you able to make known to me the dream that I saw, as well as its interpretation?"

su_text: Daniel ngawangsul, "Kangjeng Raja, kana perkawis eta, moal aya tukang sihir, jurutenung, dukun, atanapi ahli palak anu tiasa nerangkeun.

su_text: Nanging di sawarga aya nu jumeneng Allah, anu kawasa muka nu gaib-gaib, Mantenna parantos nembongkeun ka Kangjeng Raja perkawis engke ka payun.
tgt_text: However, there is a God in heaven who reveals mysteries, and he has made known to King Nebuchadnezzar what will happen in the times to come.

su_text: Sanes ku margi abdi pinter ngungkulan nu lian, nanging supados Gusti uninga kana hartosna eta impenan, sareng supados ngahartos kana pikiran-pikiran anu dongkap ka Gusti.
tgt_text: As for me, this mystery was revealed to me not because I possess more wisdom than any other living person, but so that the king may understand the interpretation and comprehend the thoughts of your mind.

su_text: Kangjeng Raja, Gusti ngimpen ningali hiji arca raksasa, herang gugurilapan, nanging bangunna pikasieuneun.
tgt_text: "You, O king, were watching as a great statue - one of impressive size and extraordinary brightness - was standing before you.

su_text: Sirahna tina emas murni, dada sareng leungeunna tina perak.
tgt_text: As for that statue, its head was of fine gold, its chest and arms were of silver, its belly and thighs were of bronze.

su_text: pingpingna tina beusi, sukuna sapalih tina beusi, sapalih tina taneuh liket.
tgt_text: Its legs were of iron; its feet were partly of iron and partly of clay.

su_text: Sapada harita keneh eta arca ngarempeyek, beusina, taneuh liketna, tambagana, perakna sareng emasna bareng ancur, bubuk lembut sapertos kekebul di tempat pangirikan di musim halodo, lajeng katiup angin, beresih teu aya urut-urutna.
tgt_text: Then the iron, clay, bronze, silver, and gold were broken in pieces without distinction and became like chaff from the summer threshing floors that the wind carries away.

su_text: Dupi batu tea wuwuh ageung, dugi ka ngajadi gunung sareng minuhan bumi sakuliahna.
tgt_text: But the stone that struck the statue became a large mountain that filled the entire earth.

su_text: Ku Allah anu jumeneng di sawarga parantos dijenengkeun raja, dipaparin kakawasaan, kagagahan, sareng kahormatan.
tgt_text: The God of heaven has granted you sovereignty, power, strength, and honor.

su_text: Kangjeng Raja, Gusti teh raja anu pangagungna ti sadaya raja-raja.
tgt_text: "You, O king, are the king of kings.

su_text: Sirah anu tina emas teh nya Gusti ku anjeun.
tgt_text: You are the head of gold.

su_text: Sapandeurieun eta, aya deui karajaan katilu, anu dilambangkeun tambaga, anu bakal ngawasaan sakuriling bumi.
tgt_text: Then a third kingdom, one of bronze, will rule in all the earth.

su_text: Saparantos eta, aya karajaan anu kaopat, anu kakiatanana lir teuasna beusi.
tgt_text: Then there will be a fourth kingdom, one strong like iron.

su_text: Sakumaha beusi kiat ngaremukkeun sareng ngancurkeun saniskanten, eta karajaan oge bakal ngaremukkeun sareng ngancurkeun karajaan-karajaan anu ti payun-payun tea.
tgt_text: Just like iron breaks in pieces and shatters everything, and as iron breaks in pieces all of these metals, so it will break in pieces and crush the others.

su_text: Nalika eta karajaan-karajaan tea ngadeg, Allah anu jumeneng di sawarga ngadegkeun hiji karajaan anu moal aya tungtungna, moal aya nu tiasa ngelehkeun, malah bakal numpes numpurkeun karajaan-karajaan anu tadi tea sadayana, lajeng ngadeg salalanggengna.
tgt_text: In the days of those kings the God of heaven will raise up an everlasting kingdom that will not be destroyed and a kingdom that will not be left to another people.

su_text: Allah anu agung parantos mintonkeun ka Gusti, hiji perkawis nu baris kajadian ka payun.
tgt_text: The great God has made known to the king what will occur in the future.

su_text: Perkawis eta, kaimpenkeunana ku Gusti aya batu ngagulundung, anu bongkar tina gunung karang kalayan teu aya anu noel-noel acan, teras neumbrag eta arca tina beusi, tambaga, taneuh liket, perak sareng emas.
tgt_text: You saw that a stone was cut from a mountain, but not by human hands; it smashed the iron, bronze, clay, silver, and gold into pieces.

su_text: Bruk Raja Nebukadnesar sujud ka Daniel.
tgt_text: Then King Nebuchadnezzar bowed down with his face to the ground and paid homage to Daniel.

su_text: Geus kitu sasauran ka Daniel, "Allah anjeun pangagungna ti sakabeh allah, Gustining raja-raja, hiji-hijina Allah anu iasa muka anu gaib-gaib.
tgt_text: The king replied to Daniel, "Certainly your God is a God of gods and Lord of kings and revealer of mysteries, for you were able to reveal this mystery!"

su_text: Ti dinya Daniel dipaparin hiji kalungguhan luhur, kitu deui dipaparin ganjaran, barang-barang nu arendah, dipaparin cangkingan di propinsi Babul tur dijadikeun kapala sakabeh jurunasehat raja.
tgt_text: Then the king elevated Daniel to high position and bestowed on him many marvelous gifts.

su_text: Daniel 3
tgt_text: Daniel 3

su_text: Tapi kalawan pamundut Daniel, eta kalungguhan pikeun nyekel pamarentahan propinsi Babul teh ku raja dicangkingkeun ka Sadrah, Mesah, jeung Abednego.
tgt_text: And at Daniel's request, the king appointed Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego over the administration of the province of Babylon.

su_text: Ari Daniel ku anjeun, tetep nyepeng kalungguhan di karaton raja.
tgt_text: Daniel himself served in the king's court.

su_text: Sim kuring, Paulus, anu ku Allah dijadikeun rasulna Kristus Yesus nyuratan, mugia aranjeun ginanjar rahmat rahayu ti Allah Rama urang jeung ti Gusti urang Yesus Kristus.
tgt_text: From Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, to the saints [in Ephesus], the faithful in Christ Jesus.

su_text: Malah ti memeh dunya gumelar, urang geus dipilih baris dijadikeun milik kagungan Mantenna ku disatunggalkeun jeung Kristus, supaya suci jeung mulus di payuneuna-Na.
tgt_text: For he chose us in Christ before the foundation of the world that we may be holy and unblemished in his sight in love.

su_text: Allah geus nangtukeun yen urang baris diangkat jadi putra-putra-Na, ku jalan Yesus Kristus.
tgt_text: He did this by predestining us to adoption as his sons through Jesus Christ, according to the pleasure of his will -

su_text: Kurnia-Na anu dipaparinkeun ka urang ku jalan Putra kaasih-Na teh kacida agungna.
tgt_text: to the praise of the glory of his grace that he has freely bestowed on us in his dearly loved Son.

su_text: Urang pangna dipilih supaya jadi umat-Na anu ngahiji jeung Kristus teh nya ku karana geus kitu tujuan Mantenna, anu geus dipastikeun ti asal mimiti pisan.
tgt_text: In Christ we too have been claimed as God's own possession, since we were predestined according to the one purpose of him who accomplishes all things according to the counsel of his will

su_text: Ku sabab kitu, urang anu pangheulana ngaharep ka Kristus, wajib muji kaagungan Allah.
tgt_text: so that we, who were the first to set our hope on Christ, would be to the praise of his glory.

su_text: Ti barang mimiti narima amanat-Na anu ngandung kayaktian, nya eta Injil Kasalametan anu bakal nyalametkeun, aranjeun teh geus jadi umat Allah, percaya ka Kristus, ku Allah diterapan cap tanda kagungana-Na nya eta Roh Suci, numutkeun jangji-Na.
tgt_text: And when you heard the word of truth (the gospel of your salvation) - when you believed in Christ - you were marked with the seal of the promised Holy Spirit,

su_text: Barang terang aranjeun geus percaya ka Gusti Yesus jeung mikanyaah ka sakumna umat Allah,
tgt_text: For this reason, because I have heard of your faith in the Lord Jesus and your love for all the saints,

su_text: Oge supaya terang rongkahna kakawasaan Mantenna anu dianggo barangdamel di urang anu percaya, nya eta kakawasaan
tgt_text: and what is the incomparable greatness of his power toward us who believe, as displayed in the exercise of his immense strength.

su_text: anu geus dianggo ngahirupkeun deui Kristus ti nu maraot jeung ngalinggihkeun Anjeunna di tengeneun Allah di sawarga.
tgt_text: This power he exercised in Christ when he raised him from the dead and seated him at his right hand in the heavenly realms

su_text: Saniskara ku Allah ditalukkeun ka Kristus anu jadi sirah gareja, jadi Gustina saniskara.
tgt_text: And Godputall things underChrist'sfeet, and he gave him to the church as head over all things.

tgt_text: Efesus 2

su_text: Lamun aya kaambek ulah katalanjuran nepi ka jadi dosa, jeung ari ambek ulah nepi ka sapoe jeput teu eureun-eureun.
tgt_text: Be angry and do not sin;do not let the sun go down on the cause of your anger.

su_text: Ulah mere kasempetan ka Iblis.
tgt_text: Do not give the devil an opportunity.

su_text: Anu geus biasa maling ulah maling deui, anggur singkil digawe nyiar napkah anu jujur, keur sorangan tur bisa dipake nulung ka batur anu eukeur kakurangan.
tgt_text: The one who steals must steal no longer; rather he must labor, doing good with his own hands, so that he may have something to share with the one who has need.

su_text: Efesus 5
tgt_text: Efesus 5

su_text: Sabalikna kudu sareh, alus budi, jeung kudu silih hampura sakumaha aranjeun oge ku Allah geus dihampura ku karana Kristus.
tgt_text: Instead, be kind to one another, compassionate, forgiving one another, just as God in Christ also forgave you.

su_text: Efesus 6
tgt_text: Efesus 6

su_text: Jeung aranjeun oge eta ayat teh aya pakaitna, nya eta: Unggal salaki kudu nyaah ka pamajikan saperti ka awak sorangan, unggal pamajikan kudu hormat ka salaki.
tgt_text: Nevertheless, each one of you must also love his own wife as he loves himself, and the wife must respect her husband.

su_text: Para panglima Persia jeung Media, kitu deui para gupernur jeung para bangsawan ti saban propinsi, araya dina eta pesta.
tgt_text: The army of Persia and Media was present, as well as the nobles and the officials of the provinces.

su_text: Dina katilu taunna jumeneng raja, anjeunna ngayakeun pesta keur para pajabat jeung gegeden-gegeden pamarentah.
tgt_text: in the third year of his reign he provided a banquet for all his officials and his servants.

su_text: Katil emas jeung katil perak ditagenkeun di palataran anu lantena ku ubin marmer bodas, ubin beureum, giwang anu gilap jeung batu pirus bulas.
tgt_text: The furnishings included linen and purple curtains hung by cords of the finest linen and purple wool on silver rings, alabaster columns, gold and silver couches displayed on a floor made of valuable stones of alabaster, mother-of-pearl, and mineral stone.

su_text: Ngarinumna teu diwates, sakumaha parentah raja ka gandek-gandek karaton, supaya anu paresta teh ngaraleueutna sasukana.
tgt_text: There were no restrictions on the drinking, for the king had instructed all of his supervisors that they should do as everyone so desired.

su_text: Ditimbalan ngangkir Ratu Wasti kalawan saged nganggo makuta ratuna.
tgt_text: to bring Queen Vashti into the king's presence wearing her royal high turban.

su_text: Juru-juru nasehat anu pangseringna disaur ku raja nya eta: Karsena, Setar, Admata, Tarsis, Meres, Marsena jeung Memukan, anu jaradi pajabat pangluhurna di karajaan Persia jeung Media.
tgt_text: Those who were closest to him were Carshena, Shethar, Admatha, Tarshish, Meres, Marsena, and Memucan.

su_text: Lahiran raja ka aranjeunna, "Kula, Raja Ahasweros, nitah gandek-gandek sangkan Ratu sina marek, Ratu teu nurut.
tgt_text: The king asked, "By law, what should be done to Queen Vashti in light of the fact that she has not obeyed the instructions of King Ahasuerus conveyed through the eunuchs?"

su_text: Memukan miunjuk ka raja jeung para pajabat, saurna, "Ratu Wasti sanes mung baha ka kersa Sang Raja, nanging ka para pajabat ongkoh, malah ka sadaya lalaki di ieu karajaan.
tgt_text: Memucan then replied to the king and the officials, "The wrong of Queen Vashti is not against the king alone, but against all the officials and all the people who are throughout all the provinces of King Ahasuerus.

su_text: Margi tangtos bakal kieu nyaranggemna, 'Raja Ahasweros geuning timbalanana ku Ratu Wasti henteu didangu.'
tgt_text: For the matter concerning the queen will spread to all the women, leading them to treat their husbands with contempt, saying, 'When King Ahasuerus gave orders to bring Queen Vashti into his presence, she would not come.'

su_text: Saparantos ieu pangumuman nyebar di sakuliah karajaan anu lega upluk-aplak, tangtos kaom wanita teh baris ngesto ka salaki, boh beunghar, boh miskin."
tgt_text: Then all the women will give honor to their husbands, from the most prominent to the lowly."

su_text: Eta pihatur kaluyuan ku raja jeung ku pajabat-pajabat.
tgt_text: The matter seemed appropriate to the king and the officials.

tgt_text: Ester 2

su_text: Ngintunkeun serat-serat ka unggal propinsi sakarajaanana nurutkeun tulisan jeung basana masing-masing, unina: Nu jadi kapala kulawarga teh nya eta salaki.
tgt_text: He sent letters throughout all the royal provinces, to each province according to its own script and to each people according to its own language, that every man should be ruling his family and should be speaking the language of his own people.

su_text: Ester 3
tgt_text: Ester 3

su_text: Eta kajadian ku raja dipiwarang dicatet dina kitab babad karajaan.
tgt_text: It was then recorded in the daily chronicles in the king's presence.

su_text: Bareto Haman, musuh urang Yahudi, anak Hamedata bangsa Agag, geus ngalung dadu anu disebut "Purim", milih poe tumpesan urang Yahudi tea, anu niatna mah rek diperenan kabeh.
tgt_text: For Haman the son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, the enemy of all the Jews, had devised plans against the Jews to destroy them.

su_text: Tapi ku sabab Ester unjukan ka raja, sarta raja ngaluarkeun parentah, niat Haman nyilakakeun urang Yahudi teh meulit ka dirina, nepi ka digantungna pisan katut ka anak-anakna.
tgt_text: But when the matter came to the king's attention, the king gave written orders that Haman's evil intentions that he had devised against the Jews should fall on his own head.

su_text: Ku sabab kitu, eta hari raya teh disebutna "Purim", hartina dadu.
tgt_text: For this reason these days are known asPurim, after the name ofpur.

su_text: Geus kitu, Ratu Ester, putra Abihail, disarengan ku Mordekai ngintun serat kalawan nganggo sagemblengna kawibawaan anjeunna, ngukuhkeun parentah perkara Purim, anu geus diparentahkeun ku Mordekai dina seratna anu ti heula.
tgt_text: So Queen Esther, the daughter of Abihail, and Mordecai the Jew wrote with full authority to confirm this second letter about Purim.

su_text: Ester 10
tgt_text: Ester 10

su_text: Sarta eta parentah Ester anu netepkeun hari raya Purim, diserat dina kitab.
tgt_text: Esther's command established these matters of Purim, and the matter was officially recorded.

su_text: Dina taun kahiji jaman Kores jadi raja Persia, PANGERAN ngabuktoskeun pangandika-Na anu ditepikeun ku Nabi Yermia.
tgt_text: In the first year of King Cyrus of Persia, in order to fulfill theLord'smessage spoken through Jeremiah, theLordstirred the mind of King Cyrus of Persia.

su_text: Kami ku Mantenna dipaparin tanggung jawab kudu ngadegkeun hiji Bait haturan Mantenna di Yerusalem, wewengkon Yuda.
tgt_text: He has instructed me to build a temple for him in Jerusalem, which is in Judah.

su_text: "Ieu parentah Kores, raja nagara Persia.
tgt_text: "Thus says King Cyrus of Persia:"'TheLordGod of heaven has given me all the kingdoms of the earth.

su_text: Maraneh kudu baralik ka Yerusalem, kudu ngadegkeun deui Bait PANGERAN Allahna Israil, Allah anu dibakti di Yerusalem.
tgt_text: Anyone from his people among you (may his God be with him!) may go up to Jerusalem, which is in Judah, and may build the temple of theLordGod of Israel - he is the God who is in Jerusalem.

su_text: Saha-saha umat Mantenna di pangbuangan butuh ku pitulung rek marulang, tatangga-tatanggana kudu ngabantu, ngabahanan perak jeung emas, bahan dahareun jeung sato-sato momot, kitu deui barang-barang pikeun baktikeuneun ka Bait Allah di Yerusalem."
tgt_text: Anyone who survives in any of those places where he is a resident foreigner must be helped by his neighbors with silver, gold, equipment, and animals, along with voluntary offerings for the temple of God which is in Jerusalem.'"

su_text: Seug kapala-kapala warga kaom Yuda jeung kaom Binyamin, para imam jeung kaom Lewi, jeung sakur anu hatena digerakkeun ku Allah, sasadiaan arek marulang, rek ngadegkeun deui Bait Allah di Yerusalem.
tgt_text: Then the leaders of Judah and Benjamin, along with the priests and the Levites - all those whose mind God had stirred - got ready to go up in order to build the temple of theLordin Jerusalem.

su_text: Tatangga-tatanggana ngabarantu, ngabahanan rupa-rupa paparabotan perak, emas, bahan dahareun, sato-sato momot, paparabotan lianna anu marahal, kitu deui barang-barang baktikeuneun ka Bait Allah.
tgt_text: All their neighbors assisted them with silver utensils, gold, equipment, animals, and expensive gifts, not to mention all the voluntary offerings.

su_text: Kores masrahkeun deui bokor-bokor jeung gelas-gelas anu ku Raja Nebukadnesar kungsi dijabel ti jero Bait Allah di Yerusalem dipake ngeusian pura dewa-dewana.
tgt_text: Then King Cyrus brought out the vessels of theLord's temple which Nebuchadnezzar had brought from Jerusalem and had displayed in the temple of his gods.

su_text: Dipasrahkeunana ku Kores ka Mitredat, bendahara karaton, anu nyatetkeun barang-barang anu rek dipulangkeun ka Sesbasar, gupernur di Yuda.
tgt_text: King Cyrus of Persia entrusted them to Mithredath the treasurer, who counted them out to Sheshbazzar the leader of the Judahite exiles.

su_text: (1:9-10) Ieu daptarna: 30 bokor emas wadah pangbakti; 1.000 bokor perak wadah pangbakti; 29 bokor lianna; 30 pinggan emas; 410 pinggan perak; 1.000 paparabotan lianna.
tgt_text: The inventory of these items was as follows:30 gold basins,1,000 silver basins,29 silver utensils,

tgt_text: Ezra 2

tgt_text: The men of Bethlehem: 123;

tgt_text: The priests: the descendants of Jedaiah (through the family of Jeshua): 973;

tgt_text: The Levites: the descendants of Jeshua and Kadmiel (through the line of Hodaviah): 74.

tgt_text: The descendants of the servants of Solomon: the descendants of Sotai, the descendants of Hassophereth, the descendants of Peruda,

tgt_text: All the temple servants and the descendants of the servants of Solomon: 392.

su_text: (2:59-60) Aya 652 anu kaasup ka golongan-golongan Delaya, golongan Tobia, jeung golongan Nekoda anu marulang ti tempat-tempat: Tel Mela, Tel Harsa, Kerub, Adan jeung Imer; tapi ngeunaan maranehna henteu aya katerangan anu tetela yen kaasup ka urang Israil.
tgt_text: These are the ones that came up from Tel Melah, Tel Harsha, Kerub, Addon, and Immer (although they were unable to certify their family connection or their ancestry, as to whether they really were from Israel):

su_text: Ku gupernur Yahudi diputuskeun yen maranehna mah teu aya hak ngadahar tina kurban suci samemeh aya imam anu ngadeg nyekel Urim jeung Tumim.
tgt_text: The governor instructed them not to eat any of the sacred food until there was a priest who could consult the Urim and Thummim.

su_text: Sanggeus daratang ka Bait Allah di Yerusalem, kapala-kapala golongan teh loba anu suka rela mere pangbakti pikeun ongkos ngadegkeun deui Bait Allah dina urutna.
tgt_text: When they came to theLord's temple in Jerusalem, some of the family leaders offered voluntary offerings for the temple of God in order to rebuild it on its site.

tgt_text: Ezra 3

tgt_text: The priests, the Levites, some of the people, the singers, the gatekeepers, and the temple servants lived in their towns, and all the rest of Israel lived in their towns.

su_text: Kaula Paulus, anu keur dibui ku karana Kristus Yesus, sareng Timoteus dulur urang.
tgt_text: From Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus, and Timothy our brother, to Philemon, our dear friend and colaborer,

su_text: ka jamaah anu kempelanana di bumi anjeun; ka Nyi Apia, sareng ka Arhipus batur saperjuangan.
tgt_text: to Apphia our sister, to Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the church that meets in your house.

su_text: Mugi di dieu sadayana aya rahmat rahayu ti Allah Rama sareng ti Gusti Yesus Kristus.
tgt_text: Grace and peace to you from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ!

su_text: Unggal kaula neneda ka Allah, anjeun ku kaula sok diunjukkeun.
tgt_text: I always thank my God as I remember you in my prayers,

su_text: reh kaula nguping yen anjeun estu percaya ka Gusti Yesus, sareng mikanyaah ka sadaya umat Allah.
tgt_text: because I hear of your faith in the Lord Jesus and your love for all the saints.

su_text: Dina paneda kaula nyuhunkeun, mugi perkawis urang jadi dulur sakapercayaan teh sing matak urang langkung surti ngalenyepan berkah-berkah anu katampi ku urang anu anut ka Kristus.
tgt_text: I pray that the faith you share with us may deepen your understanding of every blessing that belongs to you in Christ.

su_text: Ku margi kitu, dumeh kaula dulur anjeun anu sami-sami anut ka Kristus, tiasa bae kaula marentahkeun anu kedah dijalankeun ku anjeun.
tgt_text: So, although I have quite a lot of confidence in Christ and could command you to do what is proper,

su_text: Onesimus anu kapungkur taya hartosna keur anjeun, ayeuna mah malah ageung hartosna teh, boh keur anjeun boh keur kaula.
tgt_text: who was formerly useless to you, but is now useful to you and me.

su_text: mung ayeuna mah sanes sapertos bujang deui, harkatna parantos langkung ti bujang.
tgt_text: no longer as a slave, but more than a slave, as a dear brother.

su_text: Bilih bae kapungkur aya kalepatanana, atanapi aya hutangna, tempuhkeun ka kaula bae.
tgt_text: Now if he has defrauded you of anything or owes you anything, charge what he owes to me.

su_text: Tah ieu kaula nyerat kieu atuh di dieu: Kaula Paulus, anu pimayareunana.
tgt_text: I, Paul, have written this letter with my own hand: I will repay it.

su_text: Nu mawi nyeratan oge lantaran percaya anjeun bakal kersa nyumponan panuhun kaula, malah anu langkung ti eta.
tgt_text: Since I was confident that you would obey, I wrote to you, because I knew that you would do even more than what I am asking you to do.

su_text: Sajabi ti kitu kaula hayang dipangnyadiakeun kamar di dieu, lantaran aya pangarep-ngarep yen Allah bakal ngamakbul kaula bisa ka dieu deui sakumaha paneda aranjeun.
tgt_text: At the same time also, prepare a place for me to stay, for I hope that through your prayers I will be given back to you.

su_text: Aya salam ka anjeun ti Epapras anu reureujeungan dipanjara jeung kaula ku lantaran percaya ka Yesus Kristus,
tgt_text: Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, greets you.

su_text: kitu deui ti rekan-rekan kaula: Markus, Aristarkus, Demas, sareng Lukas.
tgt_text: Mark, Aristarchus, Demas and Luke, my colaborers, greet you too.

su_text: Mugia aranjeun di dieu ginanjar rahmat Gusti Yesus Kristus.
tgt_text: May the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.

su_text: Dina taun kadua Darius jadi raja Persia, dina tanggal hiji bulan anu kagenep, PANGERAN ngembankeun timbalan ka Nabi Hagai, supaya ditepikeun ka Serubabel bin Sealtiel anu jadi gupernur di tanah Yuda, jeung ka Imam Agung Yosua bin Yosadak.
tgt_text: On the first day of the sixth month of King Darius' second year, theLordspoke this message through the prophet Haggai to Zerubbabel son of Shealtiel, governor of Judah, and to the high priest Joshua son of Jehozadak:

su_text: Nabi Hagai ku PANGERAN dipiwarang nyaurkeun timbalan kieu ka umat-Na,
tgt_text: So theLordspoke through the prophet Haggai as follows:

su_text: "Eh umat Kami, ku naon maraneh geus caricing di imah nu wareweg, ari Bait Kami, burak-barik keneh?

su_text: Papakean boga, tapi teu matak haneut kana awak.

tgt_text: Moreover, I have called for a drought that will affect the fields, the hill country, the grain, new wine, fresh olive oil, and everything that grows from the ground; it also will harm people, animals, and everything they produce.'"

su_text: Mazmur 8
tgt_text: Mazmur 8

su_text: Tong diantep manusa sombong ka Gusti!
tgt_text: Don't let men be defiant!

su_text: Mazmur 10
tgt_text: (Selah) Mazmur 10

su_text: (18-44) Abdi ku Gusti diluputkeun ti jalmi-jalmi nu bangkawarah didamel kawasa ka bangsa-bangsa, jalmi-jalmi nu abdi teu wawuh, ayeuna ngawula ka abdi.
tgt_text: You rescue me from a hostile army; you make me a leader of nations; people over whom I had no authority are now my subjects.

su_text: Nun PANGERAN, Gusti nu ngersakeun abdi unggul ti musuh, nu ngaraksa ti jalmi anu barengis.
tgt_text: He delivers me from my enemies; you snatch me away from those who attack me; you rescue me from violent men.

su_text: Geus kitu Mantenna nuyun umat-Na kaluar, lir hiji pangangon.
tgt_text: Yet he brought out his people like sheep; he led them through the wilderness like a flock.

su_text: Umat-Na diaping, aman teu aya kasieun; ari musuh-musuhna mah tumpur kagulung ku laut.
tgt_text: He guided them safely along, while the sea covered their enemies.

su_text: Umat-Na dicandak ka tanah kagungana-Na nu suci, ka tanah pagunungan beunang Mantenna ngajabel.
tgt_text: He brought them to the border of his holy land, to this mountainous land which his right hand acquired.

su_text: Tanahna dibagikeun ka kaom-kaom Israil, imah-imahna diserenkeun ka umat-Na.
tgt_text: He drove the nations out from before them; he assigned them their tribal allotmentsand allowed the tribes of Israel to settle down.

su_text: Tapi umat-Na anggur ngaralawan, ngadoja ka Allah Nu Maha Kawasa, henteu narurut kana parentah-Na,
tgt_text: Yet they challenged and defied the sovereign God, and did not obey his commands.

su_text: Kemah kagungana-Na di Silo, tempat linggih-Na di tengah manusa ditilar.
tgt_text: He abandoned the sanctuary at Shiloh, the tent where he lived among men.

su_text: Imam-imam tariwas ku pedang, randa-randana teu meunang nyaleungceurikan.
tgt_text: Their priests fell by the sword, but their widows did not weep.

su_text: Musuh-musuh-Na dipukul mundur, areleh nepi ka salilana nandangan kaera.
tgt_text: He drove his enemies back; he made them a permanent target for insults.

su_text: Tapi Mantenna nolak turunan Yusup jeung teu kersaeun milih kaom Epraim.
tgt_text: He rejected the tent of Joseph; he did not choose the tribe of Ephraim.

su_text: Mantenna anggur milih kaom Yuda jeung Gunung Sion, kameumeut-Na.
tgt_text: He chose the tribe of Judah, and Mount Zion, which he loves.

su_text: Di dinya Mantenna ngadegkeun Bait-Na kawas panglinggihana-Na nu di sawarga, tohagana satohaga bumi, reugreug pageuh sapapanjangna.
tgt_text: He made his sanctuary as enduring as the heavens above; as secure as the earth, which he established permanently.

su_text: Mantenna milih abdi-Na, Daud, dicandak ti pangangonan.
tgt_text: He chose David, his servant, and took him from the sheepfolds.

su_text: Tina purah ngurus domba, Daud ku Mantenna dijieun raja Israil, anu ngangon umat Allah.
tgt_text: He took him away from following the mother sheep, and made him the shepherd of Jacob, his people, and of Israel, his chosen nation.

su_text: Mazmur 79
tgt_text: Mazmur 79

su_text: Umat Allah teh ku Daud diurus kalawan hade, diaping dijaring kalayan binangkit.
tgt_text: David cared for them with pure motives; he led them with skill.

su_text: Eta welas asih Gusti teh mugia jadi panglipur, luyu sakumaha jangji ka abdi Gusti.
tgt_text: May your loyal love console me, as you promised your servant.

su_text: Iraha bade dihukumna anu nyangsara abdi?
tgt_text: When will you judge those who pursue me?

su_text: Nun PANGERAN, pangandika Gusti teguh salalamina, langgeng abadi di sawarga.
tgt_text: O Lord, your instructions endure; they stand secure in heaven.

su_text: Gusti parantos ngadegkeun bumi, eta tetep aya.
tgt_text: You established the earth and it stood firm.

su_text: Abdi terang yen sagala rupi aya watesna, nanging aturan-aturan Gusti mah sampurna.
tgt_text: I realize that everything has its limits, but your commands are beyond full comprehension.

su_text: Parentah Gusti salamina aya dina pikiran, ngalantarankeun abdi jadi leuwih bijaksana ti batan musuh.
tgt_text: Your commandments make me wiser than my enemies, for I am always aware of them.

su_text: Pangarti abdi ngalangkungan guru-guru sorangan, margi sok ngaji aturan-aturan Gusti.
tgt_text: I have more insight than all my teachers, for I meditate on your rules.

su_text: Abdi gaduh hikmat anu langkung ti batan jalmi karolot, margi nurut kana parentah-parentah Gusti.
tgt_text: I am more discerning than those older than I, for I observe your precepts.

su_text: Abdi henteu ingkar tina parentah-parentah Gusti, margi nya Gusti anu jadi guru abdi.
tgt_text: I do not turn aside from your regulations, for you teach me.

su_text: Pangandika Gusti teh lampu pikeun abdi, sinar caang nu nyaangan jalan abdi.
tgt_text: Your word is a lamp to walk by, and a light to illumine my path.

su_text: Abdi salamina naruhkeun nyawa; nanging kana hukum Gusti tara hilap.
tgt_text: My life is in continual danger, but I do not forget your law.

su_text: Abdi ditaheunan ku jalma-jalma jahat, nanging henteu ingkar tina parentah Gusti.
tgt_text: The wicked lay a trap for me, but I do not wander from your precepts.

su_text: Tekad abdi bade tumut kana hukum-hukum dugi ka dintenan maot.
tgt_text: I am determined to obey your statutes at all times, to the very end.

su_text: Abdi cinta kana hukum Gusti, sareng ceuceub ka anu kirang satia ka Gusti.
tgt_text: I hate people with divided loyalties, but I love your law.

su_text: Abdi pasihan kakiatan sakumaha jangji Gusti, tangtos abdi bakal hirup, pangharepan abdi ulah dugi ka gaplah.
tgt_text: Sustain me as you promised, so that I will live.

su_text: Abdi cinta kana parentah-parentah Gusti langkung ti batan ka emas, ti batan ka emas nu pangkolotna.
tgt_text: For this reason I love your commands more than gold, even purest gold.

su_text: Luputkeun abdi ti nu ngagencet, sangkan tiasa ngestokeun parentah Gusti.
tgt_text: Deliver me from oppressive men, so that I can keep your precepts.

su_text: Abdi ceurik banjir cipanon, ningal jalmi-jalmi teu ngestokeun hukum Gusti.
tgt_text: Tears stream down from my eyes, because people do not keep your law.

su_text: Gusti teh adil, nun PANGERAN, hukum-hukum Gusti sadayana saestu.
tgt_text: You are just, O Lord, and your judgments are fair.

su_text: Aturan-aturan anu dipaparinkeun teh, estu adil tur sayakti.
tgt_text: The rules you impose are just, and absolutely reliable.

su_text: Amarah abdi lir seuneu ngagedur, lantaran musuh-musuh nyapirakeun parentah-parentah Gusti.
tgt_text: My zeal consumes me, for my enemies forget your instructions.

su_text: Abdi pinuh ku kasusah sareng kapaur, nanging jadi janglar ku parentah-parentah Gusti.
tgt_text: Distress and hardship confront me, yet I find delight in your commands.

su_text: Jalmi-jalmi anu karawasa narajang abdi tanpa sabab, nanging kasieun abdi mah hukum Gusti.
tgt_text: Rulers pursue me for no reason, yet I am more afraid of disobeying your instructions.

su_text: Abdi kacida ngarasa bagjana ku jangji Gusti, atoh sapertos jalmi anu manggih pependeman.
tgt_text: I rejoice in your instructions, like one who finds much plunder.

su_text: Abdi ceuceub sareng geuleuh kana bohong, sawangsulna cinta kana hukum Gusti.
tgt_text: I hate and despise deceit; I love your law.

su_text: Tujuh kali sadintenna abdi muji sukur ka Gusti, ku adilna putusan-putusan Gusti.
tgt_text: Seven times a day I praise you because of your just regulations.

su_text: Anu cinta kana hukum Gusti, kaamanana reugreug, moal aya naon-naon anu bisa ngabahyakeun maranehna.
tgt_text: Those who love your law are completely secure; nothing causes them to stumble.

su_text: Abdi ta'at kana piwulang-piwulang Gusti, leres-leres abdi cinta ka eta.
tgt_text: I keep your rules; I love them greatly.

su_text: Parentah sareng aturan Gusti parantos dilampahkeun; sagala kalakuan abdi tangtos ku Gusti katingali.
tgt_text: I keep your precepts and rules, for you are aware of everything I do.

su_text: Abdi seja nganyanyikeun hukum Gusti, margi parentah-parentah Gusti teh adil.
tgt_text: May my tongue sing about your instructions, for all your commands are just.

su_text: Gusti salamina tangtos kersa nulungan abdi, margi abdi ngestokeun parentah Gusti.
tgt_text: May your hand help me, for I choose to obey your precepts.

su_text: Abdi kumejot hayang salamet ku pitulung Gusti, nun PANGERAN, tur ngaraos bagja hirup dina hukum Gusti.
tgt_text: I long for your deliverance, O Lord; I find delight in your law.

su_text: Mazmur 120
tgt_text: Mazmur 120

su_text: Ieu pangandika PANGERAN ka Mika, urang Moreset, waktu Yotam, Ahas jeung Hiskia patuturut jumeneng raja di nagri Yuda.
tgt_text: He delivered this message during the reigns of Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah.

su_text: PANGERAN maparinkeun ieu wahyu ka anjeunna, ngeunaan sagala perkara anu tumali jeung Samaria jeung Yerusalem.
tgt_text: The prophecies pertain to Samaria and Jerusalem.

su_text: Eh bangsa-bangsa kabeh, darengekeun!
tgt_text: Listen, all you nations!

su_text: Raregepkeun ku sakabeh pangeusi bumi!
tgt_text: Pay attention, all inhabitants of earth!

su_text: Leleyuranana nyeot ka lebak-lebak, kawas cai nyeot ti lamping pasir.
tgt_text: The mountains will melt like wax in a fire, the rocks will slide down like water cascading down a steep slope.

su_text: Yerusalem sorangan!
tgt_text: They are right in Jerusalem!

su_text: Samaria, ibukotana sorangan!
tgt_text: Samaria epitomizes their rebellion!

su_text: Eta sababna PANGERAN ngandika, "Samaria ku Kami rek dijieun tumpukan barangkal di tegal, rek dijadikeun kebon anggur.
tgt_text: "I will turn Samaria into a heap of ruins in an open field - vineyards will be planted there!

su_text: Brahala-brahalana anu marahal rek diremuk-remukkeun, barang-barang pangabakti palacur-palacur kuil-kuilna kabeh rek diduruk, kitu deui arca-arca sesembahanana rek sina nalambru.
tgt_text: All her carved idols will be smashed to pieces; all her metal cult statues will be destroyed by fire.

su_text: Samaria borokna moal aya nu bisa nambaan.
tgt_text: For Samaria's disease is incurable.

su_text: Urang Saanan teu waranieun kaluar ti kotana.
tgt_text: The residents of Zaanan can't leave their city.

su_text: Mikha 2
tgt_text: Mikha 2

su_text: Maranehna bakal ngalangsud dina taneuh cara oray, kalaluar ti benteng-bentengna bari ngadegdeg kasieunan, teras darongkap ka PANGERAN, Allah abdi sadaya.
tgt_text: They will come trembling from their strongholds to the Lord our God; they will be terrified of you.

su_text: Tegalan-tegalan di Basan gararing, Gunung Karmel jadi perang, kekembangan Libanon aralum.
tgt_text: Bashan and Carmel wither; the blossom of Lebanon withers.

su_text: Maraneh tangtu diduruk, saperti rungkun cucuk nu pajeujeut, saperti jarami garing.
tgt_text: Surely they will be totally consumed like entangled thorn bushes, like the drink of drunkards, like very dry stubble.

su_text: Ti Maneh, eh Ninewe, aya saurang, nu boga niat jahat rek ngalawan ka PANGERAN.
tgt_text: From you, O Nineveh, one has marched forth who plots evil against the Lord, a wicked military strategist.

su_text: Urang Asur ku Kami keur dipangnyieunkeun kuburan, sabab maranehna teu pantes hirup!"
tgt_text: I will desecrate your grave - because you are accursed!"

su_text: Sudagar-sudagar maneh geus jadi leuwih loba ti batan bentang-bentang di langit.
tgt_text: Increase your merchants more than the stars of heaven!

su_text: dulur sim kuring anu ngaran Hanani ti tanah Yuda, datang jeung baturna sababaraha urang.
tgt_text: Hanani, who was one of my relatives, along with some of the men from Judah, came to me, and I asked them about the Jews who had escaped and had survived the exile, and about Jerusalem.

su_text: Tembok kuta Yerusalem angger ancur, gapura-gapurana ti barang tas aya nu ngahuru acan diomean deui.
tgt_text: The wall of Jerusalem lies breached, and its gates have been burned down!"

su_text: Tingali nun PANGERAN, sareng dangukeun ieu paneda abdi siang sareng wengi tina perkawis umat Gusti, bangsa Israil.
tgt_text: may your ear be attentive and your eyes be open to hear the prayer of your servant that I am praying to you today throughout both day and night on behalf of your servants the Israelites.

su_text: Tapi upama tarobat sarta ngagugu kana timbalan Kami, najan keur pabalencar nepi ka tungtung jagat oge, tan wande dipulangkeun ka tempat anu ku Kami geus dipilih geusan ngabakti ka Kami.'
tgt_text: But if you repent and obey my commandments and do them, then even if your dispersed people are in the most remote location, I will gather them from there and bring them to the place I have chosen for my name to reside.'

su_text: Nehemia 2
tgt_text: Nehemia 2

su_text: Tengah peuting eta sim kuring kaluar, dianteur ku sawatara urang.
tgt_text: I got up during the night, along with a few men who were with me.

su_text: tapi pikarepeun sim kuring ka Yerusalem anu geus diilhamkeun ku Allah, acan diomongkeun ka sasaha.
tgt_text: But I did not tell anyone what my God was putting on my heart to do for Jerusalem.

su_text: Terus maju ka kidul ka Gapura Jarian, ngaliwatan Pancuran Naga, bari nengetan kuta anu geus arurug jeung lawang-lawang anu geus lebur urut ngahuru.
tgt_text: I proceeded through the Valley Gate by night, in the direction of the Well of the Dragons and the Dung Gate, inspecting the walls of Jerusalem that had been breached and its gates that had been destroyed by fire.

su_text: Nepi ka harita, sim kuring acan nyarita naon-naon ka sasama urang Yahudi oge, boh ka imam-imam, boh ka para pamingpin jeung gegeden-gegeden, atawa ka sing saha bae anu engkena baris marilu ngabantu kana pagawean.
tgt_text: The officials did not know where I had gone or what I had been doing, for up to this point I had not told any of the Jews or the priests or the nobles or the officials or the rest of the workers.

su_text: Ku maranehna ditema kieu, "Hayu urang geura prak mimitian!" Seug maranehna tatan-tatan.
tgt_text: Then they replied, "Let's begin rebuilding right away!" So they readied themselves for this good project.

su_text: Rek barontak ka raja?"
tgt_text: Are you rebelling against the king?"

su_text: Seug maranehna nyeungseurikeun bari pokna, "Rek boga pamaksudan naon maraneh teh?
tgt_text: They said, "What is this you are doing?

su_text: Sabalikna aranjeun teu boga hak atawa milik naon bae di Yerusalem, sarta dina adat istiadat ieu kota, aranjeun teu boga bagian." Nehemia 3
tgt_text: But you have no just or ancient right in Jerusalem." Nehemia 3

su_text: Ti semet eta nepi ka tungtung bumina Elyasib, diomeanana ku Meremot bin Uria incu Hakos.
tgt_text: After him Meremoth son of Uriah, the son of Hakkoz, worked on another section from the door of Eliashib's house to the end of it.

su_text: Ditema ku Asaria bin Maaseya putu Ananya, ngomean bagian anu di payuneun bumina.
tgt_text: After them Azariah son of Maaseiah, the son of Ananiah, worked near his house.

su_text: Binyamin jeung Hasub ngomean bagian anu di payuneun bumina.
tgt_text: After them Benjamin and Hasshub worked opposite their house.

su_text: Binui bin Henadad ngomeanana ti semet bumi Asarya nepi ka pojok kuta.
tgt_text: After him Binnui son of Henadad worked on another section, from the house of Azariah to the buttress and the corner.

su_text: Hananya bin Selemya jeung Hanun, anak Salap anu kagenep, ngagarap bagian saterusna, kadua kalina.
tgt_text: After him Hananiah son of Shelemiah, and Hanun, the sixth son of Zalaph, worked on another section.

su_text: Ditema ku Mesulam bin Berekya, ngagarap anu di hareupeun imahna.
tgt_text: After them Meshullam son of Berechiah worked opposite his quarters.

su_text: Ti semet eta ka dituna digarap ku Malkia, kamasan, nepi ka wawangunan anu diparake ku kuli-kuli Bait Allah jeung ku tukang-tukang dagang, semet Gapura Mipkad, palebah loteng kuta di juru anu nyanghareup ka beulah kaler jeung wetan.
tgt_text: After him Malkijah, one of the goldsmiths, worked as far as the house of the temple servants and the traders, opposite the Inspection Gate, and up to the room above the corner.

su_text: Nehemia 4
tgt_text: Nehemia 4

su_text: (7:39-42) Daptar golongan-golongan imam anu marulang ti pangbuangan: Golongan Yedaya (turunan Yesua) 973; Golongan Imer 1.052; Golongan Pashur 1.247; Golongan Harim 1.017.
tgt_text: The priests: the descendants of Jedaiah (through the family of Jeshua), 973;

su_text: (7:43-45) Golongan-golongan urang Lewi anu marulang ti pangbuangan: Golongan Yesua jeung Kadmiel (turunan Hodawia) 74; Golongan tukang-tukang musik Bait Allah (turunan Asap) 148; Golongan tukang-tukang jaga Bait Allah (turunan Salum, Ater, Talmon, Akub, Batita jeung Sobai) 138.
tgt_text: The Levites: the descendants of Jeshua (through Kadmiel, through the line of Hodaviah), 74.

su_text: Jumlah turunan kuli-kuli Bait Allah jeung golongan abdi-abdina Suleman anu marulang ti pangbuangan aya 392.
tgt_text: All the temple servants and the descendants of the servants of Solomon, 392.

su_text: Marulangna ti Tel Mela, Tel Harsa, Kerub, Adon jeung Imer, tapi ieu mah teu bisa dibuktikeun yen turunan Israil.
tgt_text: These are the ones who came up from Tel Melah, Tel Harsha, Kerub, Addon, and Immer (although they were unable to certify their family connection or their ancestry, as to whether they were really from Israel):

su_text: Saur gupernur Yahudi maranehna mah teu meunang milu ngadahar tina kurban suci lamun can aya imam anu ngadeg nyepeng Urim jeung Tumim.
tgt_text: The governor instructed them not to eat any of the sacred food until there was a priest who could consult the Urim and Thummim.

su_text: Nehemia 8
tgt_text: Nehemia 8

su_text: Imam-imam, urang Lewi, tukang-tukang jaga Bait Allah, para pamaen musik, sajumlah rahayat biasa, kuli-kuli Bait Allah - kabeh bangsa Israil - caricingna di desa jeung di dayeuh di tanah Yuda.
tgt_text: The priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, some of the people, the temple servants, and all the rest of Israel lived in their cities.

su_text: Urang ngarurug merangan Edom!
tgt_text: Let us make war against Edom!"

su_text: Sanajan tempat maneh luhur, nepi ka siga aya di antara bentang-bentang, kawas sayang rajawali, ku Kami mo burung beunang dibedol.
tgt_text: Even if you were to soar high like an eagle, even if you were to make your nest among the stars, I can bring you down even from there!" says the Lord.

su_text: Tukang-tukang tarung urang TÃ©man bakal kasieunan, perjurit Edom kabeh bakal paraeh."
tgt_text: Your warriors will be shattered, O Teman, so that everyone will be destroyed from Esau's mountain!

su_text: "Ku sabab maneh geus ngarampog, jeung maehan turunan Yakub, dulur-dulur sorangan, maneh bakal dibasmi, bakal nista sapapanjangna.
tgt_text: "Because you violently slaughtered your relatives, the people of Jacob, shame will cover you, and you will be destroyed forever.

su_text: Nenjo dulur-dulur di Yuda meunang musibat, kuduna maneh ulah mupuas.
tgt_text: You should not have rejoiced over the people of Judah when they were destroyed.

su_text: "Tapi di gunung Sion bakal aya nu bisa rahayu, sarta eta gunung bakal jadi tempat suci.
tgt_text: But on Mount Zion there will be a remnant of those who escape,and it will be a holy place once again.

su_text: Turunan Yakub baris ngabogaan deui tanah pusakana.
tgt_text: The descendants of Jacob will conquerthose who had conquered them.

su_text: Turunan Yakub jeung turunan Yusup bakal kawas seuneu, bakal ngabasmi turunan Esau kawas seuneu ngaduruk jarami.
tgt_text: The descendants of Jacob will be a fire, and the descendants of Joseph a flame.

su_text: Turunan Esau mo aya nu bisa ngejat.
tgt_text: The descendants of Esau will be like stubble.

su_text: Urang Israil bakal ngamilik wewengkon Epraim jeung Samaria.
tgt_text: They will also take possession of the territory of Ephraim and the territory of Samaria, and the people of Benjamin will take possession of Gilead.

su_text: Ieu teh sabda Ki Pandita, putra Daud, raja di Yerusalem.
tgt_text: The words of the Teacher, the son of David, king in Jerusalem:

su_text: Turunan nu ieu datang, turunan nu itu undur, sabalikna jagat mah tetep-tumetep.
tgt_text: A generation comes and a generation goes, but the earth remains the same through the ages.

su_text: Angin nyewuk ka kidul, nyewuk ka kaler, putar-puter bulak-balik.
tgt_text: The wind goes to the south and circles around to the north; round and round the wind goes and on its rounds it returns.

su_text: Walungan kabeh bahena ka laut, bet laut teu pinuh-pinuh.
tgt_text: All the streams flow into the sea, but the sea is not full, and to the place where the streams flow, there they will flow again.

su_text: Kana kajadian baheula-baheula hamo aya anu inget, pon kitu jaman anu masih bakal datang moal kaingetkeun ku anu harirupna sabada jaman eta.
tgt_text: No one remembers the former events, nor will anyone remember the events that are yet to happen; they will not be remembered by the future generations.

su_text: Kami, Ahli Pikir, raja nu nyangking Israil di Yerusalem.
tgt_text: I, the Teacher, have been king over Israel in Jerusalem.

su_text: Kami geus gilig seja nguji jeung nalungtik sagala anu enggeus kajadian di kolong langit.
tgt_text: I decided to carefully and thoroughly examine all that has been accomplished on earth.

su_text: Anu bingkeng taya anu bisa ngalelempeng, anu teu aya euweuh anu bisa milang.
tgt_text: What is bent cannot be straightened, and what is missing cannot be supplied.

su_text: Ceuk hate, "Aing teh nya agung nya pinter, leuwih ti nu sejen-sejen anu geus ti hareula jenengna raja di Israil, beunghar ku hikmah pinuh ku pangaweruh."
tgt_text: I thought to myself, "I have become much wiser than any of my predecessors who ruled over Jerusalem; I have acquired much wisdom and knowledge."

su_text: Pengkhotbah 2
tgt_text: Pengkhotbah 2

su_text: Horeng jelema mah beuki pinter teh beuki loba kasalempang, beuki loba kanyaho beuki loba kahariwang.
tgt_text: For with great wisdom comes great frustration; whoever increases his knowledge merely increases his heartache.

su_text: Turug-turug saha anu nyaho, naha pijelemaeunana teh nu bijaksana atawa nu gejul.
tgt_text: Who knows if he will be a wise man or a fool?

su_text: Ngingetkeun ka dinyana mah buntu wae harepan kana sagala hasil usaha beunang soson-soson di alam dunya teh.
tgt_text: So I began to despair about all the fruit of my labor for which I worked so hard on earth.

su_text: Anu matak jelema mah panghadena teh geus bae nyatu nginum, beubeunangan usaha teh pake senang-senang.
tgt_text: There is nothing better for people than to eat and drink, and to find enjoyment in their work.

su_text: Cik, saha jelemana anu bisa lubak-libuk ku dahareun atawa bisa senang-senang, lamun henteu direjekian ku Mantenna?
tgt_text: For no one can eat and drink or experience joy apart from him.

su_text: Pengkhotbah 3
tgt_text: Pengkhotbah 3

su_text: Kapan boh hikmah jeung pangaweruh, boh kasenangan, dipaparinkeunana ku Allah teh ka jelema anu dipikaseneng ku Mantenna.
